### Login - Execute primeiro para obter o token
# @name login
POST http://localhost:8081/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@studio.com",
  "senha": "Admin@2026!"
}

### Pegar token da resposta do login (para VS Code REST Client)
# @token = {{login.response.body.token}}

### Cadastrar usuário (apenas ADMIN)
POST http://localhost:8081/api/auth/cadastro
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "email": "funcionario@studio.com",
  "senha": "Func@2026!",
  "role": "FUNCIONARIO",
  "funcionarioId": 1
}

### Obter usuário atual
GET http://localhost:8081/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Listar usuários
GET http://localhost:8081/api/auth/usuarios
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Buscar usuário por ID
GET http://localhost:8081/api/auth/usuarios/4
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Atualizar usuário
PUT http://localhost:8081/api/auth/usuarios/1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "email": "",
  "role": ""
}

### Trocar senha
PUT http://localhost:8081/api/auth/usuarios/1/trocar-senha
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "senhaAtual": "Admin@2026!",
  "novaSenha": "NovaSenha@2026!"
}

